  "name": "Anticipate Dodge",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/dodge.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Your knowledge of mobility and your attack prowess allow you to thwart elusive opponents.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Dodge, Mobility; base attack bonus +7, brawler level 4th, or monk level 4th.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>You automatically know whether a creature you can see has a dodge bonus to its AC. You gain up to a +2 bonus on attack rolls against a target that has a dodge bonus. This bonus cannot exceed the dodge bonus of the creature you attack.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>You can spend 1 stamina point to increase the maximum bonus from Anticipate Dodge by 2 (this is still limited by the creature's dodge bonus, however).",
